<Link id="l00242" /><CodeLine lineNumber="242"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Given a processed operand Op which was promoted to a larger integer type,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00243" /><CodeLine lineNumber="243"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// this returns the promoted value. The low bits of the promoted value</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00244" /><CodeLine lineNumber="244"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// corresponding to the original type are exactly equal to Op.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="245"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The extra bits contain rubbish, so the promoted value may need to be zero-</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00541" /><CodeLine lineNumber="541"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// GetSoftenedFloat - Given a processed operand Op which was converted to an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00542" /><CodeLine lineNumber="542"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// integer of the same size, this returns the integer.  The integer contains</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00543" /><CodeLine lineNumber="543"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// exactly the same bits as Op - only the type changed.  For example, if Op</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00544" /><CodeLine lineNumber="544"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// is an f32 which was softened to an i32, then this method returns an i32,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00545" /><CodeLine lineNumber="545"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// the bits of which coincide with those of Op</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00546" /><CodeLine lineNumber="546"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64isellowering-cpp/#a51cb24bd3e700fcf2f93d1afbb555a16">SDValue</a> GetSoftenedFloat(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64isellowering-cpp/#a51cb24bd3e700fcf2f93d1afbb555a16">SDValue</a> Op) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00547" /><CodeLine lineNumber="547"><span class="doxyHighlight">    TableId <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/amdgpu/vgprindexmode/#a9afd95476c40096a5898ba0f06370b3a">Id</a> = getTableId(Op);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00548" /><CodeLine lineNumber="548"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-cskyconstantislandpass-cpp-/#a0bd7d621ba8de56e4052df49da823802">Iter</a> = SoftenedFloats.find(Id);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00549" /><CodeLine lineNumber="549"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Iter == SoftenedFloats.end()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00550" /><CodeLine lineNumber="550"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(isSimpleLegalType(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/amdgpu/sendmsg/#a8594419a4ddfad2c9a79279c490e466d">Op</a>.getValueType()) &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00551" /><CodeLine lineNumber="551"><span class="doxyHighlight">             </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;Operand wasn&#39;t converted to integer?&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00552" /><CodeLine lineNumber="552"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/amdgpu/sendmsg/#a8594419a4ddfad2c9a79279c490e466d">Op</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00553" /><CodeLine lineNumber="553"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00554" /><CodeLine lineNumber="554"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64isellowering-cpp/#a51cb24bd3e700fcf2f93d1afbb555a16">SDValue</a> SoftenedOp = getSDValue(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-cskyconstantislandpass-cpp-/#a0bd7d621ba8de56e4052df49da823802">Iter</a>-&gt;second);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01008" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1008"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Given a processed vector Op which was widened into a larger vector, this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1009"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// method returns the larger vector. The elements of the returned vector</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1010"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// consist of the elements of Op followed by elements containing rubbish.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1011"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// For example, if Op is a v2i32 that was widened to a v4i32, then this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1012"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// method returns a v4i32 for which the first two elements are the same as</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1013"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// those of Op, while the last two elements contain rubbish.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1014"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64isellowering-cpp/#a51cb24bd3e700fcf2f93d1afbb555a16">SDValue</a> GetWidenedVector(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64isellowering-cpp/#a51cb24bd3e700fcf2f93d1afbb555a16">SDValue</a> Op) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1015"><span class="doxyHighlight">    TableId &amp;WidenedId = WidenedVectors&#91;getTableId(Op)&#93;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1016"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64isellowering-cpp/#a51cb24bd3e700fcf2f93d1afbb555a16">SDValue</a> WidenedOp = getSDValue(WidenedId);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1017"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(WidenedOp.getNode() &amp;&amp; </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;Operand wasn&#39;t widened?&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01018" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1018"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> WidenedOp;</span></CodeLine>
